```json
{
  "application": "PBS",
  "details": {
    "resource_requirements": {
      "cores": "4, 4, 5, 6, 8, 8, 8, 12, 12, 20, 24",
      "mpi_processes": "2, 1, 1, 1, 4, 2, 1, 6, 2, 2, 2",
      "gpus": "1",
      "memory": "1GB",
      "walltime": "00:05:00",
      "queue": "short_gpuQ"
    },
    "software_dependencies": [
      "gcc91",
      "openmpi-3.0.0",
      "BLAS",
      "gsl-2.5",
      "lapack-3.7.0",
      "cuda-11.3",
      "gromacs"
    ],
    "script_purpose": "This script appears to be creating PBS (Portable Batch System) job submission files for running molecular dynamics simulations using GROMACS with different numbers of cores and MPI processes on a GPU cluster.",
    "input_files": [
      "template.pbs",
      "md_meta.tpr",
      "meta.dat"
    ],
    "output_files": [
      "md_${n_cores[i]}_${n_mpiprocs[i]}_out",
      "md_${n_cores[i]}_${n_mpiprocs[i]}_err"
    ],
    "environment_variables": [
      "OMP_NUM_THREADS"
    ]
  }
}
```
